 'description': 'Original Checkmk plugin (through v1.0.2) created by '
                'wellingtonsilva67@gmail.com. This plugin uses agent_modbus '
                'v2.1 as its data source, developed by Vincent Tacquet '
                '(https://github.com/vtacquet/agent_modbus). Set the Server '
                'Address, port, slave and the registers you want to query from '
                'the device. Consult the device documentation to find out '
                'which registers you want and test them via command line '
                'before configuring the services in the web interface. Version '
                '1.0.10 is an internal refactor with no user-facing config '
                'changes: WARN/CRIT evaluation now uses the documented '
                'cmk.agent_based.v2.check_levels() helper instead of a '
                'hand-rolled comparison, and an internal rule-spec variable '
                'was renamed for clarity. Visible effects, both coming from '
                'the helper itself: the "(warn/crit ...)" text now appears '
                'before the "(<cid>)" suffix instead of after it, and it now '
                'says "at" for an upper breach vs "below" for a lower one '
                '(previously always "at"). Version 1.0.9 adds optional '
                '"levels_upper"/"levels_lower" WARN/CRIT thresholds to the '
                '"Modbus register value scaling" rule, so services can go '
                'WARN/CRIT (e.g. low battery, overheating) instead of always '
                'being OK. Version 1.0.8 adds a configurable "unit" suffix '
                '(e.g. "%", " °C") and a "signed" 16-bit two\'s complement '
                'option to the "Modbus register value scaling" rule, so '
                'registers like battery/temperature/humidity sensors can be '
                'displayed with the correct unit and sign. Version 1.0.7 fixes '
                'multiple Modbus slaves on one host for real: Checkmk only '
                'ever keeps one data source per special agent name per host, '
                'so yielding one command per slave (1.0.4-1.0.6) only ever ran '
                'the last slave - all Modbus slaves configured in the rule are '
                'now queried by a single agent_modbus invocation that loops '
                'over them internally and tolerates individual slave failures. '
                'Version 1.0.4 changed the "Check Modbus devices" rule so a '
                'single rule can configure several Modbus slaves. Version '
                '1.0.3 fixed the value parser and added a "Modbus register '
                'value scaling" rule to display/graph values with decimal '
                'places. This Checkmk plugin (rulesets, server_side_calls and '
                'check logic) was adapted and is maintained by Felipe Soares '
                '(https://github.com/felipesoaresti/).',
